quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  2,197,"The Hajj is in known months, then whoever sets out to the Hajj during them (should know that) there shall be no sexual conduct, and no disobedience (of God commands), and no argument (or altercation) during the Hajj. And whatever good you do, God knows it. And take provision, and indeed the best provision is self control (against unlawful desires and sins). And People of understanding, be cautious of Me"
  2,198,"There is no blame on you to look for your Master's bounty (through trades), and when you return from (mount) Arafat then remember God at the Sacred Monument. And remember Him, as He guided you, though previously you were of the misguided"
  2,199,Then proceed from where the people are proceeding and ask for God’s forgiveness. He is forgiving and merciful
  2,200,"And when you completed your rituals then remember God as you remember your fathers, or remember more. And among the people some say: our Master, give us (good things) in this world. There is no share for him in the hereafter"
  2,201,"And among them, some say: our Master, give us good in this world and good in the hereafter, and protect us from the punishment of the fire"
  2,202,They have benefit of whatever they did. God is quick in accounting
  2,203,"And remember God in the specified days (during the Hajj). Anyone who hurries up for two days, there is no sin against him and anyone who delays (for two days) there is no sin against him, of course for anyone who controls himself. And be cautious of God and know that you will be gathered before Him"
  2,204,"And there is one among the people who impresses you with his word about this world’s life, and he calls God to witness about what is in his heart, while he is the most determined enemy"
  2,205,"When he gains authority (or turns away) he tries, on the earth, to corrupt it and destroys the crops and the offspring. God does not like the corruption"
  2,206,"And when he is told to be cautious of God, the egotism leads him to the sin. So hell is enough for him, it is a bad resting place"
  2,207,"While some among people gives his life looking for God's pleasure, and God is gentle to his servants"
  2,208,"You who believe, enter into submission (to God), all of you, and do not follow the steps of Satan as he is indeed your obvious enemy"
  2,209,"But if you stumbled after clear proofs came to you, know that God is powerful and wise"
  2,210,"Do they wait for God and the angels to come to them in shades of the clouds, and then the matter is settled? All matters are returned to God"